ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. J. R. NO. 1067 Page 1

1 BE I T RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES AND THE SENATE OF THE
2 2ND SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
3 SECTION 1. The Secretary of State shall refer to the people for
4 their approval or rejection, as and in the manner provided by law,
5 the following proposed amendment to Section 2 of Article XXV-A of
6 the Oklahoma Constitution to read as follows:
7 Section 2. A. In addition to those otherwise eligible for
8 medical assistance under Oklahoma’s Medicaid program, the State
9 shall, until the conditions described in subsection C of this
10 section occur, provide medical assistance under Oklahoma’s Medicaid
11 program to Low Income Adults.
12 B. No greater or additional burdens or restrictions on
13 eligibility or enrollment shall be imposed on persons eligible for
14 medical assistance pursuant to this Article than on any other
15 population eligible for medical assistance under Oklahoma’s Medicaid
16 program.
17 C. If the federal medical assistance percentage (FMAP)
18 established under 42 U.S.C., Section 1396d(y) is reduced below
19 ninety percent (90%), then the duty imposed on the State by
20 subsection A of this section shall cease to have effect,
21 notwithstanding any subsequent increases to such FMAP; provided,
22 however, this subsection shall not be construed to prohibit the
23 Legislature from enacting laws to provide Medicaid coverage to Low
24 Income Adults.
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. J. R. NO. 1067 Page 2

1 SECTION 2. The proposed Constitutional amendment as set forth
2 in SECTION 1 of this resolution shall not become effective if the
3 State Question resulting from Enrolled House Bill No. 4440 of the
4 2nd Session of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature is approved by the
5 people, as certified by the Secretary of State.
6 SECTION 3. The Ballot Title for the proposed Constitutional
7 amendment as set forth in SECTION 1 of this resolution shall be in
8 the following form:
9 BALLOT TITLE
10 Legislative Referendum No. ____ State Question No. ____
11 THE GIST OF THE PROPOSITION IS AS FOLLOWS:
12 This measure amends the Oklahoma Constitution. It amends
13 Section 2 of Article 25-A to state that if the federal medical
14 assistance percentage (FMAP) for Medicaid expansion drops below
15 ninety percent, then the State’s constitutional duty to cover
16 Low Income Adults under Oklahoma’s Medicaid program will end,
17 regardless of any later increases to the FMAP. It clarifies
18 that this measure does not prohibit the Legislature from passing
19 laws to provide Medicaid coverage to Low Income Adults. This
20 measure states that if the State Question resulting from
21 Enrolled House Bill No. 4440 of the 2nd Session of the 60th
22 Oklahoma Legislature is approved by the people, then this
23 Constitutional amendment shall not become effective.
24 SHALL THE PROPOSAL BE APPROVED?
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. J. R. NO. 1067 Page 3

1 FOR THE PROPOSAL — YES _____________
2 AGAINST THE PROPOSAL — NO _____________
3 SECTION 4. The Chief Clerk of the House of Representatives,
4 immediately after the passage of this measure, shall prepare and
5 file one copy thereof, including the Ballot Title set forth in
6 SECTION 3 hereof, with the Secretary of State and one copy with the
7 Attorney General.”
